						               													<description>Max 4 Players (solo variant to multiplayer variant)&amp;#10;the game has a setup of Tile laying (every time a new random Board is created using hexagon terrain tiles)and Actual movement of chasing elephants after on the terrain with the advantage of the terrain and the player character&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Co-operative resource placement of the operational component&amp;#10;Co-operative actions to capture the wild elephant (3 wild elephants out of 4 elephants)&amp;#10;Random elephant movement (4 X 2 (custom dice) directional dice to work this mechanism on direction and no of places to move in that direction)&amp;#10;Placement of campsites (only in the first turn) and Capture mechanism by a player in subsequent rounds as actions by the player&amp;#10;Placement of capture mechanism by each player every round (excluding some terrain and based on terrain type.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once all the player places the mechanism is done. a random player rolls the dice(Elephant movement dice) using Dice tower and based on the outcome the elephants move towards the indicated direction&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If there is an obstacle it cannot move that direction(excluding a few obstacles and group movements)&amp;#10;The game continues until all or min 3 elephants move to Khedda or all campsites destroyed by the movement of elephants(Detailed rules on win is there in the rulebook)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
